>Any recommendations for an Integrated Development Environment (IDE) for a
new user of ocaml >under Microsoft Windows ?

If you have / can afford Microsoft Visual C++, there is a OCaml Project
Wizard available at http://tech.motion-twin.com . If you need OCaml syntax
highlight, have a look at
http://www.codeguru.com/tips/user_def_keywords.shtml

Other solutions are :
- to use a "can-edit-all-that-you-want" IDE, write your own OCaml mode and
use OCamake to compile
- use emacs !

Nicolas Cannasse

